The President of the United States expresses concern over the violence in Egypt, which has resulted in the loss of life among demonstrators and security forces. The US offers condolences to the affected families and stands with the Egyptian people during this difficult time. The statement emphasizes the need for restraint from all sides, so that Egyptians can work together to build a strong and united nation. The US believes in the importance of respecting the rights of minorities, including Copts, and supports peaceful protest and religious freedom. The statement also mentions Prime Minister Sharaf's call for an investigation and urges all parties to refrain from violence. Despite these tragic events, the US encourages timely elections and a peaceful transition to democracy that is fair and inclusive.